The extra constant dimension with value 1 generates the unimodal and bimodal dynamics. Each neural coordinate (zl, zv, za) can be seen as a 3-D point in the 3-fold Cartesian space defined by the language, visual, and acoustic embeddings dimensions [zl1]T , [zv1]T , and [za1]T .
This definition is mathematically equivalent to a differentiable outer product between zl, the visual representation zv, and the acoustic representation za.
